# Local dev workflow

Default to dev watch startup. Do not spend time on manual `pnpm build` or `pnpm clean:dist && pnpm build` unless dist is provably corrupted.

## Start Gateway (default)

```bash
pnpm gateway:watch:raw
```

Alternative: `pnpm dev gateway --force`

`scripts/run-node.mjs` auto-builds stale or missing `dist/` with incremental tsdown (`--no-clean`), then starts Gateway. Source changes trigger rebuild + restart.

## Do not (normal dev)

- Run `pnpm build` or `pnpm clean:dist` before starting Gateway
- Run `pnpm build` while Gateway or `gateway:watch` is running
- Run multiple build paths at once (`pnpm build` + `pnpm openclaw ...` + watch)

Concurrent or overlapping builds corrupt hashed `dist/` chunks and cause `ERR_MODULE_NOT_FOUND`.

## When clean build is allowed

Only after confirmed dist corruption (e.g. `Cannot find module '.../dist/<hash>.js'` with Gateway already stopped):

```bash
pkill -f "run-node.mjs gateway"   # stop watch first
pnpm clean:dist && pnpm build
pnpm gateway:watch:raw
```

Do not suggest or run clean build for routine dev, first startup, or slow tsdown output alone.

## Control UI

- `gateway:watch` does not rebuild Control UI assets
- After UI changes: `pnpm ui:build` or `pnpm ui:dev`
